<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-13T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2611</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-13T21:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President has been prevailed upon, to sign mandate dissolving
                            Parliament which was today countersigned by newly appointed acting
                            Premier, the General of Peking Gendarmerie. Although the mandate
                            mentions an early election of new Parliament, it is probably not
                            satisfactory to the South.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>